; FOUND by P6d numeric-depth sweep (ESH-0125). Bignum quotient/remainder are
; silently WRONG once both operands are bignums: the fundamental division
; identity a = q*b + r fails. remainder is off by a small delta at moderate
; scale; at larger scale the quotient is wrong too.
;   a=10^25 b=7^25 : (remainder a b) off by 128, (= a (+ (* q b) r)) is #f
(require stdlib)
(define a (expt 10 25))
(define b (expt 7 25))
(define q (quotient a b))
(define r (remainder a b))
(define ok (= a (+ (* q b) r)))
(if ok (begin (display "OK divmod-bignum") (newline))
       (begin (display "FAIL divmod-bignum a<>q*b+r") (newline)))
